===Etymology===
From {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|δῆμος||people}} + {{m|grc|ὄνυμα||name}}. Possibly coined or revived in 1997 by Paul Dickson of [[w:Merriam-Webster|Merriam-Webster]] in a manner similar to other "nyms".

{{confix|demo|onym|lang=en}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈdɛmənɪm/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A name for an [[inhabitant]] or [[native]] of a [[specific]] [[place]], usually derived from the [[name]] of the place.
#: ''Why is it that people from the United States use American as ''their'' '''demonym'''?''
# {{lb|en|obsolete}} A [[pseudonym]] formed of an [[adjective]].
#: ''The Logophile has my favourite '''demonym'''; I would write under it if he didn't.''

